I absolutely loved this place! My friend and I decided to go and check the place out for the first time and we were not disappointed. The Nopal tacos were perfectly grilled and seasoned, the sopes were so detailed, it has beans on the base with chicken and fresh toppings on top for some crunch. We thought the food was delicious. In addition, the customer service was so on point, he made sure we had enough chips, the right salsas and even recommended a dessert that was shareable between my friend and I. I give this place a 10/10, you won’t regret going. I was very happy with everything and will totally be going there again!

Liquor license is pending, so no margaritas, which was very dissatisfying. Guacamole, prepared at your desired level of "heat" (mild, medium or hot) in a crock, lined with fresh lime juice, was delicious and worth the visit. Fajitas-type dish for 2, with chicken, steak, shrimp and chorizo, was disappointing because steak was well done and tough and chicken was on the dry side.  Management apologized and explained the overcooking was a result of the pot's maintaining heat to keep the food hot and warm.  Since this is the case, chef should compensate by adjusting the cook time. Management also stated that other steak dishes could be ordered to your desire. I'm certain there are other dishes that are good and merit an average 4+ star rating, as indicated on Google, so I would go back and try again, when I'm in the area and have a desire for Mexican food.

All of the tacos here are AMAZING! All topped with onions and cilantro. They make their tortillas in house daily and heat them on the griddle. The octopus taco was my second favorite. The texture was perfect and paired well with a slightly spicy salsa. Chorizo was a close 3rd place, which was perfectly delicious with no salsa at all. The lengua taco had good flavor nice texture, but was a bit dry. The barbacoa (goat) taco was very goat-y, so if you love goat you will love this taco. Extremely friendly servers and staff. They have Mexican Coca-Cola, Jarritos, and daily aqua frescos. Check this place out. We went for lunch and the dining room was packed. They have a separate side of the restaurant just for take out, which is genius. I will definitely be going back here soon.

The steak burrito I had at Habanero was easily the best burrito I've had in just over 20 years since I lived in California. It was bursting with flavor from the first bite to the last. The tomatillo salsa was excellent and had just the right amount of heat.  The burrito was so good I wished it were larger, but it wasn't small either. It included guacamole which I understand they make at your table right in front of you. Perhaps that occurs during the day as I went there in the evening and simply saw a sign that was put away.  I held the San Francisco area burritos as the gold standard but Habanero's may have topped the list. I asked for a few lime wedges and they were willingly provided. Habanero's is an excellent addition to the plethora of culinary choices we have in College Park. Once you visit you'll become a regular.  Advice to management is get a sign ASAP, and put the burritos on the menu. Their omission and the lack of a sign left me scratching my head. Also, your cashiers should be well versed in the product. Every time I asked a question she had to get the answer from someone else. She was nice though.  I highly recommend Habanero's if you're a fan of Mexican food. their burritos are the best. I've not tried anything else but I have no reason to doubt anything I have will be superb. I'll be going back again soon. One last thing, their prices are competitive, not cheap and not expensive.
